27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_mmu_nv04.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");

29#include "nv04.h"
30
31#include <core/gpuobj.h>
32
33#define NV04_PDMA_SIZE (128 * 1024 * 1024)
34#define NV04_PDMA_PAGE ( 4 * 1024)
35
36/*******************************************************************************
37 * VM map/unmap callbacks
38 ******************************************************************************/
39
40static void
41nv04_vm_map_sg(struct nvkm_vma *vma, struct nvkm_memory *pgt,
42 struct nvkm_mem *mem, u32 pte, u32 cnt, dma_addr_t *list)
43{
44 pte = 0x00008 + (pte * 4);
45 nvkm_kmap(pgt);
46 while (cnt) {
47 u32 page = PAGE_SIZE / NV04_PDMA_PAGE;
48 u32 phys = (u32)*list++;
49 while (cnt && page--) {
50 nvkm_wo32(pgt, pte, phys | 3);
51 phys += NV04_PDMA_PAGE;
52 pte += 4;
53 cnt -= 1;
54 }
55 }
56 nvkm_done(pgt);
57}
58
59static void
60nv04_vm_unmap(struct nvkm_vma *vma, struct nvkm_memory *pgt, u32 pte, u32 cnt)
61{
62 pte = 0x00008 + (pte * 4);
63 nvkm_kmap(pgt);
64 while (cnt--) {
65 nvkm_wo32(pgt, pte, 0x00000000);
66 pte += 4;
67 }
68 nvkm_done(pgt);
69}
70
71static void
72nv04_vm_flush(struct nvkm_vm *vm)
73{
74}
75
76/*******************************************************************************
77 * MMU subdev
78 ******************************************************************************/
79
80static int
81nv04_mmu_oneinit(struct nvkm_mmu *base)
82{
83 struct nv04_mmu *mmu = nv04_mmu(base);
84 struct nvkm_device *device = mmu->base.subdev.device;
85 struct nvkm_memory *dma;
86 int ret;
87
88 ret = nvkm_vm_create(&mmu->base, 0, NV04_PDMA_SIZE, 0, 4096, NULL,
89 &mmu->vm);
90 if (ret)
91 return ret;
92
93 ret = nvkm_memory_new(device, NVKM_MEM_TARGET_INST,
94 (NV04_PDMA_SIZE / NV04_PDMA_PAGE) * 4 + 8,
95 16, true, &dma);
96 mmu->vm->pgt[0].mem[0] = dma;
97 mmu->vm->pgt[0].refcount[0] = 1;
98 if (ret)
99 return ret;
100
101 nvkm_kmap(dma);
102 nvkm_wo32(dma, 0x00000, 0x0002103d); /* PCI, RW, PT, !LN */
103 nvkm_wo32(dma, 0x00004, NV04_PDMA_SIZE - 1);
104 nvkm_done(dma);
105 return 0;
106}
107
108void *
109nv04_mmu_dtor(struct nvkm_mmu *base)
110{
111 struct nv04_mmu *mmu = nv04_mmu(base);
112 struct nvkm_device *device = mmu->base.subdev.device;
113 if (mmu->vm) {
114 nvkm_memory_del(&mmu->vm->pgt[0].mem[0]);
115 nvkm_vm_ref(NULL, &mmu->vm, NULL);
116 }
117 if (mmu->nullp) {
118#ifdef __NetBSD__
119 const bus_dma_tag_t dmat = device->func->dma_tag(device);
120 bus_dmamap_unload(dmat, mmu->nullmap);
121 bus_dmamem_unmap(dmat, mmu->nullp, 16 * 1024);
122 bus_dmamap_destroy(dmat, mmu->nullmap);
123 bus_dmamem_free(dmat, &mmu->nullseg, 1);
124#else
125 dma_free_coherent(device->dev, 16 * 1024,
126 mmu->nullp, mmu->null);
127#endif
128 }
129 return mmu;
130}
131
132int
133nv04_mmu_new_(const struct nvkm_mmu_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
134 int index, struct nvkm_mmu **pmmu)
135{
136 struct nv04_mmu *mmu;
137 if (!(mmu = kzalloc(sizeof(*mmu), GFP_KERNEL)))
138 return -ENOMEM;
139 *pmmu = &mmu->base;
140 nvkm_mmu_ctor(func, device, index, &mmu->base);
141 return 0;
142}
143
144const struct nvkm_mmu_func
145nv04_mmu = {
146 .oneinit = nv04_mmu_oneinit,
147 .dtor = nv04_mmu_dtor,
148 .limit = NV04_PDMA_SIZE,
149 .dma_bits = 32,
150 .pgt_bits = 32 - 12,
151 .spg_shift = 12,
152 .lpg_shift = 12,
153 .map_sg = nv04_vm_map_sg,
154 .unmap = nv04_vm_unmap,
155 .flush = nv04_vm_flush,
156};
157
158int
159nv04_mmu_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_mmu **pmmu)
160{
161 return nv04_mmu_new_(&nv04_mmu, device, index, pmmu);
162}
